article.headline: CS Northridge 70, UC Davis 60
article.story: LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Mike Efevberha scored 22 points and Jonathan Heard added 15 to lead Cal State Northridge to a 70-60 win over UC Davis on Thursday. The Matadors (7-8) shot 44.7 percent from the field and Efevberha, who averages 20 points per game, was 6-of-15 from the floor. Thomas Juillerat scored 14 points to lead UC Davis (5-12), which shot just under 32 percent for the game. Northridge led at halftime 35-26 and started the second half with a 9-0 run that opened its lead to 18 with 18:23 to play. Juillerat scored nine points in a row and cut the lead to 50-40 with 12:47 remaining. The game was marred by three Northridge technical fouls and four UC Davis players who fouled out of the game. Northridge starting forward Calvin Chitwood left the game early in the first half with a bloody nose after he dove for the ball. He returned a short time later and finished with 10 points.
